# Recruitment App - Complete Product Specification

## Executive Summary
This is a B2B sales-focused recruitment app that helps users identify companies hiring, qualify them as potential clients, and reach out to decision-makers. The app bridges the gap between job discovery and business development.

---

## Core Concept Clarification

**Your Users Are**: Recruiters/agencies looking for clients (companies)  
**The Clients Are**: Companies with open positions  
**The Contacts Are**: Decision-makers (hiring managers, HR directors, CTOs) at those companies  

This is a **two-level hierarchy system**: Companies ‚Üí Decision Makers

---

## Pages & Navigation Structure

### 1. **Job Feed** (Discovery Page)
Primary entry point for finding new opportunities

**Purpose**: Browse and filter LinkedIn-scraped jobs to identify potential client companies

**Key Elements**:
- **Search & Filters**
  - Keywords
  - Location
  - Industry
  - Company size
  - Date posted
  - Saved filters for quick access
  
- **Job Card Display** (List/Grid view toggle)
  - Company logo and name
  - Job title
  - Location
  - Posted date
  - Key requirements snippet
  - Quick action: "Add to Pipeline" button
  - "View Details" link
  
- **Pagination** or infinite scroll
- **Bulk Actions**: Select multiple jobs to add at once

**User Flow**:
```
Browse ‚Üí Filter ‚Üí Click "Add to Pipeline" ‚Üí Job saved to Companies
```

---

### 2. **Companies** (Main Workspace)
Central hub for managing potential client relationships

**Purpose**: Manage all companies you're pursuing as clients

**Key Elements**:

- **View Options**
  - List view (default)
  - Kanban board view (by status)
  - Table view with sorting
  
- **Filters & Search**
  - Status filter (Researching, Qualified, Outreach Started, Engaged, Won, Lost)
  - Date added
  - Industry
  - Number of contacts
  - Last activity
  - Search by company name
  
- **Company Card/Row** displays:
  - Company name + logo
  - Source job title
  - Status badge (color-coded)
  - Number of decision makers found
  - Last activity timestamp
  - Quick actions: View Detail, Archive, Add Note
  
- **Quick Stats Dashboard** (top of page)
  - Total companies in pipeline
  - By status breakdown
  - Contacts messaged this week
  - Response rate

**Status Pipeline**:
1. **New** - Just added, needs research
2. **Researching** - Gathering info about company
3. **Qualified** - Good fit, ready for outreach
4. **Outreach Started** - Messages sent to decision makers
5. **Engaged** - Decision makers responded
6. **Won** - Became a client
7. **Lost** - Not interested/no response

---

### 3. **Company Detail Page** (The Power Page)
Where all the action happens for a specific company

**Purpose**: Research, qualify, and execute outreach for one company

**Layout**: Split-screen or tabbed interface

#### **Section A: Company Overview** (Left/Top)
- Company name, logo, website
- Industry, size, location
- **Source Job Details**:
  - Job title
  - Description
  - Requirements
  - Salary (if available)
- **Company Research** (manual or AI-scraped):
  - About the company
  - Recent news
  - Tech stack
  - Company culture notes
- **Qualification Section**:
  - Why they're a good fit (editable notes)
  - "Qualify Company" button ‚Üí triggers decision maker scraping
  - Qualification checklist (optional)

#### **Section B: Decision Makers** (Right/Bottom)
- **Contact Cards** (displayed after qualification):
  - Photo (from LinkedIn)
  - Name
  - Title/Role
  - LinkedIn profile link
  - Department
  - Status badge (Not Contacted, Messaged, Responded, Unresponsive)
  - "Message" button
  
- **Bulk Actions**: Select multiple contacts to message at once

#### **Section C: Outreach Center**
- **Message Generation**:
  - Select decision maker(s)
  - AI generates personalized message based on:
    - Their role
    - Company needs (from job posting)
    - Your services
  - Preview message
  - Edit message
  - "Send via LinkedIn" or "Copy to Clipboard"
  
- **Outreach History**:
  - Timeline of all messages sent
  - Who was contacted
  - When
  - Response status
  - Follow-up reminders

#### **Section D: Activity Log**
- All actions taken on this company
- Notes added
- Status changes
- Messages sent
- Responses received

**User Flow**:
```
View Company ‚Üí Review Job + Company Info ‚Üí Click "Qualify" ‚Üí 
System scrapes decision makers ‚Üí Review contacts ‚Üí 
Select contacts ‚Üí Generate personalized messages ‚Üí Send ‚Üí 
Track responses
```

---

### 4. **All Contacts** (Secondary View)
Global view of all decision makers across all companies

**Purpose**: 
- Avoid duplicate outreach
- Manage follow-ups across companies
- Find specific people

**Key Elements**:

- **Table View** with columns:
  - Contact name + photo
  - Title
  - Company (clickable to Company Detail)
  - Industry
  - Outreach status
  - Last contact date
  - Next follow-up date
  - Quick actions: Message, View Company, Add Note
  
- **Advanced Filters**:
  - By outreach status
  - By company
  - By title/role (CTOs, HR Directors, etc.)
  - By response status
  - Date ranges
  - Custom tags
  
- **Search**: By name, company, title

- **Bulk Actions**:
  - Send follow-up messages
  - Update status
  - Add tags
  - Export to CSV

**Key Use Cases**:
- "Show me everyone I messaged last week who hasn't responded"
- "Find all HR Directors I haven't contacted yet"
- "List everyone at companies in 'Engaged' status"

---

### 5. **Analytics/Reports** (Optional but Recommended)
Data-driven insights into your pipeline

**Key Metrics**:
- **Pipeline Health**:
  - Companies by status
  - Time spent in each stage
  - Conversion rates between stages
  
- **Outreach Performance**:
  - Messages sent per week/month
  - Response rate
  - Average time to response
  - Best performing message templates
  
- **Source Analysis**:
  - Which job types lead to best clients
  - Which industries respond best
  - LinkedIn vs other sources
  
- **Charts/Graphs**:
  - Pipeline funnel visualization
  - Response rate trends
  - Activity timeline

---

## Key Features & Functionality

### Core Features

#### 1. **Job Scraping & Import**
- Automated LinkedIn job scraping
- Filter jobs before importing
- Bulk import capabilities
- Deduplication (avoid adding same company twice)

#### 2. **Company Management**
Contact management allows CRM systems to help companies organize and manage their business contacts, including contact details, communication records, special requests or preferences, and reminders to reach out periodically

- Custom fields for company data
- Status tracking through pipeline stages
- Notes and tags
- Activity history

#### 3. **Decision Maker Scraping**
- Automated LinkedIn scraping after qualification
- Extract: name, title, photo, profile URL
- Department/role identification
- Senior/junior level detection

#### 4. **AI Message Generation**
- Personalized per decision maker role
- Context-aware (uses job description + company info)
- Editable templates
- A/B testing capability (future)

#### 5. **Outreach Tracking**
Tools that provide tracking and reporting are essential for performance analysis, allowing users to evaluate outcomes effectively and track metrics such as conversion rates and response patterns

- Message status tracking
- Response detection (manual marking)
- Follow-up reminders
- Communication history

#### 6. **Search & Filtering**
Look for features that allow you to track customer interactions, segment leads, and automate follow-up processes, ensuring your sales team can focus on high-value opportunities

- Global search across companies and contacts
- Advanced filtering options
- Saved searches/filters
- Boolean search for contacts (optional)

---

## UI/UX Design Guidelines

### Design Principles

#### 1. **Minimal & Clean**
Modern CRM UI design should include minimalist and clean layouts for reduced clutter, customizable dashboards tailored to user needs, and dark mode with accessibility-friendly features

- Lots of white space
- Avoid over-designing
- Focus on clarity and speed
- Functionality over flair

#### 2. **Status-Driven Design**
- Color-coded status badges:
  - **Gray**: New/Researching
  - **Blue**: Qualified
  - **Yellow**: Outreach Started
  - **Green**: Engaged/Won
  - **Red**: Lost/Unresponsive
- Visual pipeline with drag-and-drop

#### 3. **Card-Based Layouts**
- Use cards for:
  - Job listings
  - Company entries
  - Decision maker profiles
- Hover states with quick actions
- Progressive disclosure (show more on expand)

#### 4. **Quick Actions Philosophy**
Every task should be minimal clicks:
- Add job to pipeline: **1 click**
- Qualify company: **1-2 clicks**
- Generate + send message: **2-3 clicks**
- View all contacts: **1 click**

### Visual Style

**Color Palette**:
- Primary action color (one accent - e.g., blue/purple)
- Neutral grays for backgrounds (#F9FAFB, #F3F4F6)
- Status colors (as mentioned above)
- Text: #111827 (dark), #6B7280 (medium), #9CA3AF (light)

**Typography**:
- Modern sans-serif (Inter, Roboto, System UI)
- Clear hierarchy (32px ‚Üí 24px ‚Üí 18px ‚Üí 16px ‚Üí 14px)
- Plenty of line-height for readability

**Components**:
- Rounded corners (4-8px)
- Subtle shadows for cards
- Clear focus states
- Smooth transitions (200-300ms)

**Responsive**:
- Desktop-first (primary use case)
- Mobile-friendly for on-the-go checking
- Tablet-optimized for reviewing on iPad

---

## Data Structure

### Database Schema

#### Companies Table
```
- id (primary key)
- name
- logo_url
- website
- industry
- size
- location
- source_job_id (foreign key)
- status (enum)
- qualification_notes
- created_at
- updated_at
- last_activity_at
- is_archived
```

#### Jobs Table
```
- id (primary key)
- title
- description
- requirements
- company_name (before company created)
- location
- posted_date
- source_url (LinkedIn)
- salary_range
- is_added_to_pipeline
- created_at
```

#### Contacts Table (Decision Makers)
```
- id (primary key)
- company_id (foreign key)
- name
- title
- department
- linkedin_url
- photo_url
- email (if available)
- phone (if available)
- seniority_level
- outreach_status (enum)
- created_at
- updated_at
```

#### Messages Table
```
- id (primary key)
- contact_id (foreign key)
- company_id (foreign key)
- message_content
- sent_date
- response_received
- response_date
- response_content
- channel (LinkedIn, Email, etc.)
- created_at
```

#### Activities Table (Audit Log)
```
- id (primary key)
- company_id (foreign key)
- contact_id (nullable)
- activity_type (note_added, status_changed, message_sent, etc.)
- description
- created_by (user_id)
- created_at
```

---

## User Workflows

### Workflow 1: From Job Discovery to First Outreach
```
1. Land on Job Feed
2. Apply filters (e.g., "Engineering roles in San Francisco")
3. Browse job cards
4. Click "Add to Pipeline" on 3-5 interesting jobs
5. Go to Companies page
6. Click first company to open Company Detail
7. Review job description and company info
8. Add qualification notes ("Great fit - they need React developers")
9. Click "Qualify Company"
10. System scrapes and displays 5 decision makers
11. Review decision makers (CTO, Engineering Manager, HR Director)
12. Select CTO and Engineering Manager
13. Click "Generate Messages"
14. AI creates personalized messages for each
15. Review and edit messages
16. Click "Send" or "Copy to Clipboard"
17. Mark as sent
18. Company status automatically updates to "Outreach Started"
```

### Workflow 2: Follow-Up Management
```
1. Go to All Contacts page
2. Filter by "Messaged" + "No Response" + "Sent 7+ days ago"
3. Select multiple contacts
4. Click "Generate Follow-Up Messages"
5. Review batch-generated follow-ups
6. Send follow-ups
7. Set reminder for next follow-up in 1 week
```

### Workflow 3: Response Handling
```
1. Receive LinkedIn response from a decision maker
2. Go to All Contacts page
3. Search for person's name
4. Click their profile
5. Goes to Company Detail page (contact highlighted)
6. Click "Mark as Responded"
7. Add response notes in activity log
8. Company status updates to "Engaged"
9. Schedule next follow-up action
```

