## Technical Recommendations

### Tech Stack Suggestions

**Frontend**:
- React + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Shadcn/ui for components
- React Query for data fetching
- Zustand or Redux for state management

**Backend**:
- Node.js + Express or Next.js API routes
- PostgreSQL for database
- Prisma ORM
- Redis for caching

**Scraping**:
- Puppeteer or Playwright for LinkedIn scraping
- Bright Data or Apify for reliable scraping
- Rate limiting and proxy rotation

**AI Integration**:
- OpenAI API or Anthropic Claude API for message generation
- Prompt templates for consistency
- User context injection

**Hosting**:
- Vercel or Railway for easy deployment
- AWS S3 for file storage
- Cloudflare for CDN

---

## Success Metrics

### Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

**User Engagement**:
- Daily/weekly active users
- Average time spent in app
- Jobs added per user per week
- Companies qualified per user per week

**Conversion Metrics**:
- Jobs ‚Üí Companies conversion rate
- Companies ‚Üí Qualified conversion rate
- Qualified ‚Üí Outreach conversion rate
- Outreach ‚Üí Response rate
- Response ‚Üí Client conversion rate

**Efficiency Metrics**:
- Time from job discovery to first outreach
- Average messages sent per user per week
- User retention rate (7-day, 30-day)

---

## Competitive Differentiation

### What Makes This Unique

1. **Job-to-Client Pipeline**: Most recruitment tools focus on candidate placement, not client acquisition
2. **Decision Maker Focus**: Automatically finds the right people to contact, not just companies
3. **AI Personalization**: Messages tailored to each decision maker's role and company needs
4. **Lightweight**: Not a full ATS - focused specifically on business development
5. **LinkedIn-First**: Built around how recruiters actually source new business

### Compared to Traditional CRMs
- ‚úÖ Pre-populated with job/company data (no manual entry)
- ‚úÖ Automated decision maker discovery
- ‚úÖ Industry-specific (recruitment) workflows
- ‚úÖ AI message generation built-in

### Compared to Recruitment ATSs
- ‚úÖ Focused on client acquisition, not candidate management
- ‚úÖ Lighter weight, faster to get value
- ‚úÖ Lower cost
- ‚úÖ Easier learning curve

